race.comment: GAZELLE (11) is knocking on the door, beaten narrowly in her last two. Gets in light with the claim and is drawn to get the gun run. Ready to strike. TORRITA (9) sets up well after missing the bob last time at long odds, lipped by the heavy favourite. Another who gets in light with the claim and looks ready to peak. OAK PARK MADDISON (12) comes through the same race, where she was disappointing but almost too bad to be true. Her first two runs of the prep were full of merit, so she's worth forgiving. SMOTHER (3) resumes for the Hickmott camp and has been readied with a Strathalbyn trial. Has found the maiden win elusive but any improvement during the break will see him competitive. BARGAIN BOY (4) is another likely improver and can be kept safe.
